    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix websrv_end() function to prevent crashes and memory leaks\n\n### Summary\nThe `websrv_end()` function in the web server implementation had several issues that could lead to crashes and memory leaks. This PR addresses these issues by adding proper NULL checks and cleanup procedures.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/websrv/websrv.c`: Enhanced `websrv_end()` function with NULL pointer checks before calling ulfius functions, proper handling of `dummy_telnetsrv_params` memory management, and resetting the `websrvparams` structure to avoid stale pointers.\n- `common/utils/websrv/websrv.h`: Added function declaration for `websrv_end()` to make it part of the public API.\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Start the web server using `websrv_autoinit()`\n2. Call `websrv_end()` with a NULL pointer or after the web server has already been stopped\n3. Observe potential crash due to NULL pointer dereference or memory leak due to improper cleanup\n\n### Symptoms\n- Segmentation fault when calling `websrv_end()` with NULL parameter\n- Memory leaks when `dummy_telnetsrv_params` is not properly freed\n- Stale pointer issues when restarting the web server after calling `websrv_end()`\n\n"
}